items.text: The hand made noodle at e last roll is goooood...
Try the coffee at yi xuan cha Shi 01-01! Like awesome woohoo :D
warong hjh kamisah nasi ayam penyet! 10!
Bak chor mee. Teochew Kway Teow Soup 01-43 serves it Teochew-style. Simple basic preparation. Clean tastes of the ingredients
The golden barn confectionary muffins are worth it, soft, creamy and delicious
Chai tow kway (fried carrot cake): Compared A) Kim Lee #01-30 & B) Shun Li #01-25 side-by-side. A wins hands down for more fragrance & taste (tks to lots of 'chai por' -chopped fermented radish)
Tai Dong Teochew Duck Rice - the duck is tender and nice. Very good
Try the ayam penyet at Kedai Mak Nyai
Must try #01-73 好萊塢鴨飯.鴨粥
Yong Xiang Prawn Noodle... always order mee pok dry... nicey
Mutton Briyani @ Kedai Mak Nyai - Tues and Thurs only
Mohd Sabir Muslim Food, maggie goreng is not very nice.
Prawn noodle, Xiong ji kitchen must try. Also the rooster chicken. There fried chicken v gd.
Sakkan teh..1 is never enough! :)
Vegetarian options: Nonya kueh, local desserts, chwee kueh, yam cake, nasi jagong, prata, thosai, lontong, fried carrot cake, fruits, beancurd, specialty vegetarian stall, yong tau foo, cheecheongfun
好吃再来 is nice!!! must try (^_-)
Zhen Xiang Fish Soup!
Prawn noodles: Stall #01-36 is 1 of d rare few in SG still serving d crunchy kangkong (water spinach) in their prawn noodles. Soup was light yet full of flavours. For $3, portion was generous!
go for Jin Feng Nasi Lemak! and order their specialty: cereal chicken
Good fish soup @ market stall, #01-60, Lai You Hai Xian
Nain Food Stall is the best  cheap & good food serving place
Tai Dong duck rice stall is the best here.
Must try Xiong Ji Kitchen #01-03 
Duck rice/noodles: What I enjoyed most was Hollywood's (#01-73) succulent duck meat. Cooked until its soft enuf, d meat tastes delicate in ur mouth. It's also nice dat it's not too herbal
go to 好吃再来 food stall... their food nice n cheap!!! :D
Concern Western Food a quality western stall nt to be missed!
Very crowded between 12 - 1.30pm
Ayampenyet
Bak kut Teh is not bad...!
Try warong Rahmah muslim food nasi lemak- $1.50 only
Many good stalls. Try, try everything! :)
Home to the tastiest tapioca cakes. Thin and crispy gets my vote!  Also great soya bean drink, look out for the stall with the long queues
Hainanese curry rice: Dun hv too high expectation if u c a q @ Havelock Hainanese Curry Rice #01-70. All very charmg & old-school (variety of dishes, elderly man in singlet) but taste below ave :-(
kim lee carrot cake the white stuff is not to be miss: p
Saleem masala tea *thumbs up*
Thumbs up for Masala teh from Saleem teh tarik
Fresh veg  available  tues to sun
Try the seafood noodle from hock heng cooked food stall..it's nice
Nearest ATMs. Mkt is Blk 49. UOB is @ Blk 48. DBS/POSB is across rd @ Blk 52. OCBC is @ Blk 53
Concern Western Food #01-16 very good chicken chop
Traditional
The Jin Feng very nice ley!!! (Y)
The fried round tapioca kueh that 4SQ user Phoebe referred to is found at 01-69. Consistently sold out, so be patient, very patient
Today I'm having some noodles for breakfast. There's this Kim Lee carrot cake here which I really like but it's closed today though soooo...
The sugarcane store facing the road is probably the best in town(: cuz they seriously don add any sugar syrup
Hollywood duck rice! Must try!
Nearest POSB/DBS ATM is across the road at void deck of Blk 52
Soon Lee Lou Fried Carrot Cake is yumz #01-25 they sell out fast
Prawn noodle soup & dry  #01-36
Must try the Golden Rooster Western Food. They cook the chicken so nice and they are Halal. ^_^
Try the sugar cane drink facing the road. Probably the coolest drink for hot weather! They have some poems on the side signboard.
try Mohd Sabir Muslim Food, maggie goreng 
Drink kopi at Heng wang kopi stall. Best kopi you will get here
Havelock Hainanese Curry Rice is damn nice here!
Try Loo Kee Soup Fish Porridge Stall . Nice soup 
Try the chicken mayo at #01-22
New stall "Hollywood Duck Rice" has a long history from "Hollywood Theater Canteen", and is a MUST EAT!
Delicious Nasi Lemak & Economic Fried Bee Hoon at Xiang Xiang. #01-35
I went for the nasi lemak - mayo chicken, cheese sausage , long beans $3.50
Nain Food Stall... Malay Nasi Padang... #01-07
must buycheap n good
Nice food here: fish soup (super long queue) steamed soup near the main road
Hokkien mee!!!
Sliced fish soup. I wd rank 1) Hock Heng #01-31, 2) Lai You #01-60, & 3) Loo Kee #01-71. HH's fish slices & soup r thick & generous. LY has a robust soup base, despite serving thin fish slices
Check out Saleem teh tarik!
Soy sauce steam fish 
There's this soya bean drink stall where it boasts a q. Tried but it turned out only ordinary. Try the duck rice next to hup lee economic bee hoon. Not bad.
Try the see kee wan tan mee! Very delicious
The yong tau foo standard is horrible.
Foods here are simply value for money & nice.
The market I grew up with
Metal spikes on roosting areas. Simple, non-chemical, non-harming method to keep birds (mainly pigeons, mynahs & crowd) away
Soya bean drink stall #01-27. standard had drop, like drinking water.
Don't miss the freshly-made 'soon kueh' here. Radish fillings comes with mushrooms. The 'kuchai kueh' and pink 'png kueh' also nice. Taste like homemade.
Wantan Mee. Hui Ji #01-35 is generous with ingredients but noodle sauce is bland (w/o chilli). Their Lor Mee is also popular
Fierce but cool ..,,,
